Summaries for PCCB Gene

Entrez Gene Summary for PCCB Gene

  • The protein encoded by this gene is a subunit of the propionyl-CoA carboxylase (PCC) enzyme, which is involved in the catabolism of propionyl-CoA. PCC is a mitochondrial enzyme that probably acts as a dodecamer of six alpha subunits and six beta subunits. This gene encodes the beta subunit of PCC. Defects in this gene are a cause of propionic acidemia type II (PA-2). Multiple transcript variants encoding different isoforms have been found for this gene.[provided by RefSeq, May 2010]

GeneCards Summary for PCCB Gene

PCCB (Propionyl-CoA Carboxylase Beta Subunit) is a Protein Coding gene. Diseases associated with PCCB include propionicacidemia and pccb-related propionic acidemia. Among its related pathways are Carbon metabolism and Glyoxylate and dicarboxylate metabolism. GO annotations related to this gene include ligase activity and propionyl-CoA carboxylase activity. An important paralog of this gene is MCCC2.

No data available for UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot , Tocris Summary , Gene Wiki entry , PharmGKB "VIP" Summary , fRNAdb sequence ontologies and piRNA Summary for PCCB Gene
